        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 6:40PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 640 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 11 miles northeast of Cope to near Bethune.
Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

These storms will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Yuma
and northeastern Kit Carson Counties, including the following
locations... Joes, Kirk, and Idalia.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 424 and 434, and near
mile marker 441.
Highway 385 between mile markers 187 and 211.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
northeastern and east central Colorado.</instruction>
